{|{{Infobox ship begin}} {{Infobox ship image |Ship image=[[File:HMS M 20.JPG|300px|M 20]] |Ship caption= }} {{Infobox ship career |Hide header= |Ship country= |Ship flag= {{shipboxflag|Sweden|naval}} |Ship name= ''M 20'' |Ship namesake= |Ship ordered= |Ship builder= |Ship laid down= |Ship launched= 1941 |Ship acquired= |Ship commissioned=18 December 1941 |Ship decommissioned=2005 |Ship in service= |Ship out of service= |Ship struck= |Ship reinstated= |Ship homeport= |Ship motto= |Ship nickname= |Ship honours= |Ship fate= |Ship status=Museum ship |Ship notes= }} {{Infobox ship characteristics |Hide header= |Header caption= |Ship class= |Ship type= [[Minesweeper (ship)|Minesweeper]] |Ship displacement= {{convert|70|LT|t|0|abbr=on}} |Ship length= {{convert|27|m|ftin|abbr=on}} |Ship beam= {{convert|5|m|ftin|abbr=on}} |Ship draught= {{convert|1.5|m|ftin|abbr=on}} |Ship propulsion= |Ship speed= {{convert|13|kn|lk=in}} |Ship range= |Ship complement= |Ship sensors= |Ship EW= |Ship armament=• 1× [[Oerlikon 20 mm cannon|20 mm cannon]] |Ship armour= |Ship notes= }} |} '''HSwMS ''M 20''''' was a [[Minesweeper (ship)|minesweeper]] that served in the [[Swedish Navy]]. Built in 1941 of [[mahogany]] on a steel frame, ''M 20'' represents legendary shipbuilding and was in service from 1941 until 2005.
Decommissioned in 2005 she is now owned by SMM (Swedish Maritime Museums) and operated and maintained by the association "Föreningen M 20".
